  "prompt": "What is the average Outbrain's CTR for marketers?",
  "response": "The average click-through rate (CTR) for Outbrain campaigns can vary widely depending on several factors, including the industry, targeting, ad creatives, and the quality of the content being promoted. However, as a general benchmark, Outbrain has reported that a **CTR of 0.1% to 0.3%** is considered average for content discovery campaigns.\n\nFor marketers, achieving a higher CTR often involves optimizing ad creatives, using compelling headlines, targeting the right audience, and ensuring that the landing pages are relevant and engaging. Some highly optimized campaigns may achieve CTRs above 0.5%, but this is less common.\n\nIt's important to note that CTR is just one metric, and marketers should also focus on other performance indicators like cost per click (CPC), conversion rates, and return on ad spend (ROAS) to evaluate the overall success of their campaigns.",
